title.narrative: COMPLETION OF A FULL CYCLE OF COMPULSORY INCLUSIVE EDUCATION FOR ALL CHILDREN

description.narrative: By 2022, adolescents and youth increased skills and competencies to be adequately prepared for adult life as active citizens and for the world of work., which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Learning Outcomes, Learning Outcomes (Covid), Skills Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, all children and adolescents in Ukraine, especially those disadvantaged and affected by the conflict, access inclusive and quality school education and early learning while enjoying opportunities for meaningful participation and civic engagement.

description.narrative: In 2019 UNICEF with education in emergency (EiE) response have reached 38,400 vulnerable school and preschool age children in NGCA and in areas along the contact line in GCA (0-20km), providing them with education supplies, school furniture, sports equipment, rehabilitating schools that are in the most critical need and building capacity of 680 teachers on identified priority topics (Life Skills Education (LSE), Conflict Sensitive Education (CSE), Disaster Risk Reduction (DRR). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2020
